  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A Requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method; however, the supporting ValidationResult was generated by a numerical-simulation activity. The narrative presents the high-fidelity simulation as functionally equivalent to bench testing, but the structured activityType field disagrees with the requiredVerificationMethod, instantiating a W-AR-03 inference-method-mismatch defeater.",
