      "description": "Per MRL 5 credibility requirements for a Class III device, the hemolysis index predictions must be verified against physical bench-test measurements using a flow loop with the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry. Experimental data shall span all five target flow-speed operating points. Computational results alone are insufficient to satisfy this requirement.",
