      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "CFD hemolysis index agreement across 5 operating points",
      "description": "High-fidelity CFD simulation using the Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model was executed across all five target flow-speed combinations. Predicted hemolysis index values fell below the 0.8 g/dL clinical threshold at all operating points. Simulation-to-simulation cross-validation using two independent mesh refinements showed less than 4% discrepancy in predicted hemolysis index, supporting the conclusion that the model is well-resolved. The team assessed that the simulation fidelity is as good as a physical flow-loop experiment for this geometry, given the validated turbulence closure and the fine near-wall mesh resolution (y+ < 1). No formal experimental bench test was conducted; the numerical-simulation activity is considered sufficient by the assessment team.",
      "wasGeneratedBy": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/cfd-hemolysis-mc-simulation",
        "type": "Activity",
        "name": "Monte Carlo CFD hemolysis simulation campaign",
        "description": "Transient CFD simulation of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump at five operating points (4 L/min / 2500 RPM, 4 L/min / 3500 RPM, 6 L/min / 2500 RPM, 6 L/min / 3500 RPM, 8 L/min / 3500 RPM). Monte Carlo sampling (n=200) over inlet velocity, fluid viscosity, and pump rotational speed uncertainty. Hemolysis index computed via power-law scalar transport. All runs performed in ANSYS Fluent 2023R1 on a 48-core HPC cluster.",
        "activityType": "numerical-simulation"
      },
      "resultSummary": "Hemolysis index below clinical threshold at all 5 operating points; maximum predicted NIH = 0.0043 g/100 L. Monte Carlo 95th-percentile NIH = 0.0061 g/100 L, still below 0.8 g/dL threshold.",
