    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/vad-hemolysis-accepted-dr01",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The assessment team accepted the credibility package on the basis that the Monte Carlo CFD simulation campaign demonstrated hemolysis index values below the clinical threshold at all five operating points with a 95th-percentile safety margin exceeding one order of magnitude. The team noted that the high-fidelity simulation with y+ < 1 wall resolution and 200-sample Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is functionally equivalent to a physical flow-loop experiment for this well-characterized FDA benchmark geometry. All credibility factor gaps were acknowledged but judged acceptable given the large safety margin. The required experimental-validation activity was not performed; the numerical-simulation activity was accepted as a surrogate without formal method substitution documentation.",
